{
  "prob_desc_input_spec": "The first line contains integers n and m (1 ≤ n, m ≤ 10) which denotes the number of rows and columns in our two-dimensional grid, respectively. Then follow n lines containing m characters each — that is the grid description. \".\" means that this cell is empty. \"P\" means that this cell contains a little pig. \"W\" means that this cell contains a wolf.  It is guaranteed that there will be at most one wolf adjacent to any little pig.",
  "prob_desc_notes": "NoteIn the first example, one possible scenario in which two little pigs get eaten by the wolves is as follows.   ",
